Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 532 224 with 81 340 cases reported by China. There are now a total of 450 884 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 202 countries/locations outside mainland China, representing an increase of 60 752 cases when compared with the data on 25 Mar 2020, with the USA accounting for 17 173 (27.3%) cases, Italy accounting for 6203 (10.2%) cases, and Spain for 8271 (13.6%) of the newly confirmed cases. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside of China now represents 84/7% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA now represents 16.1% of the global cases of COVID-19. The USA has surpassed China in total number of cases, with Italy to do the same tomorrow (27 Mar 2020). A global total of 24 087 deaths have been reported, 20 795 (86.3%) outside mainland China.

It is now clear that while China has the largest population in the world, and was the original location where the COVID-19 outbreak started, it has markedly reduced transmission to a manageable level, now monitoring all arrivals in the country from outside. South Korea has slowly decreased daily new case counts hovering around or below 100 in recent days. The USA is now number one outside of China for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19 and Italy will be number 2 by tomorrow (27 Mar 2020). Iran has slowed down in growth rate and Spain has been accelerating. To get an understanding of how rapidly things increase, look at the last 3 entries to the "greater than 1000 cases list (Thailand, Romania, and Saudi Arabia). The doubling time from approximately 500 to 1000 cases was between 4-5 days.

I repeat my request to see epidemic curves by date of onset to see what the true curve of transmission is, as I suspect now that more testing is being done, many of those tested have been sick for days while awaiting testing. - Mod.MPP]

