[2] China: National Health Commission 26 Mar 2020
Date: Thu 26 Mar 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202003/c521093a01734df3b3fbc156064ba19f.shtml


At 04:00 on [26 Mar 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 55 new confirmed cases, of which 54 were imported cases abroad, 1 was a local case (1 in Zhejiang); 5 new deaths were reported (5 in Hubei) and 49 new suspected cases.

On the same day, 537 new cases were cured and discharged, 837 were close contacts under medical observation, and 201 severe cases improved.

As of 24:00 on [26 Mar 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there were 3460 confirmed cases (including 1034 severe cases), 74 588 cured cases, and 3292 deaths. A total of 81 340 confirmed cases have been reported and 189 suspected cases have been reported. A total of 697 470 close contacts have been tracked and 16 005 close contacts are still under medical observation.

There were 0 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (0 in Wuhan), 530 newly cured cases (523 in Wuhan), 5 new deaths (4 in Wuhan), and 2896 confirmed cases (2880 in Wuhan). Among them, there were 999 severe cases (995 in Wuhan). A total of 61 731 discharged patients (44 591 in Wuhan) were cured, a total of 3174 deaths (in Wuhan, 2535), and a total of 67 801 confirmed cases (in Wuhan, 50 006). There were 0 new suspected cases (0 in Wuhan) and 0 existing suspected cases (0 in Wuhan).

At 04:00 on [26 Mar 2020], 54 newly diagnosed imported cases were reported (17 in Shanghai, 12 in Guangdong, 4 in Beijing, 4 in Tianjin, 3 in Inner Mongolia, 3 in Zhejiang, 3 in Fujian, and 2 in Shandong, 2 in Yunnan, 1 in Liaoning, 1 in Jiangsu, 1 in Sichuan, and 1 in Shaanxi). As of 24:00 on [26 Mar 2020], a total of 595 confirmed imported cases were reported overseas.

A total of 738 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 453 cases in Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (110 cases discharged, 4 deaths), 33 cases in Macau Special Administrative Region (10 cases discharged), and 252 cases in Taiwan (29 cases discharged, 2 deaths).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[This is the 3rd consecutive day with no newly confirmed cases reported from Wuhan or all of Hubei province in the past 24 hours, but now 49 suspected cases are reported, having reported no suspected cases yesterday (25 Mar 2020). Only 1 non-importation case was reported. There are 55 newly confirmed cases reported to have been confirmed in the past 24 hours, all but one were importation related.

According to the report above, a total of 81 340 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from mainland China, representing an increase of 55 cases in the past 24 hours since yesterday's (25 Mar 2020) report was prepared. In addition, 5 deaths were reported, all in Hubei province (4 in Wuhan). 43 new cases were reported from Hong Kong, which bears watching as the cases have been slowly but steadily climbing. And Macau reported 3 additional newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours, bringing their total to 30.

Of the 55 newly confirmed cases, 54 were imported cases into China. Cases were reported by Shanghai (17), Guangdong (12), Beijing (4), Tianjin (4), Inner Mongolia (3), Zhejiang (3), Fujian (3), and Shandong (2), Yunnan (2), Liaoning (1), Jiangsu (1), Sichuan (1), and Shaanxi (1) bringing the total number of imported cases to 595.

As reported on 24 Mar 2020, China ended the lockdown in Hubei and will end it in Wuhan on 6 Apr 2020. There is much caution and skepticism in the media over the reality of the zero case reports. The world will be watching carefully to see if this is safe timing...

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html, and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7149046,155. - Mod.MPP]

