Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Spain has been rapidly accelerating in terms of transmission of the SARS-CoV-2. As of today (26 Mar 2020), there have been a total of 56 188 cases with 8578 cases confirmed in the preceding 24 hours. The countrywide 2-week incidence per 100 000 population is 113.03. It is now 2nd in Europe, behind Italy, and 3rd globally behind the USA and Italy.

Reviewing the tables and data from Section [1] above (and prior posts) above, on 2 Feb 2020 there had only been 1 case reported, by 1 Mar 2020, there were 84 cases, in 1 week, by 8 Mar 2020 there were 673 cases, in another week by 15 Mar 2020 there were 7845 cases, by 22 Mar 2020 there were 28 768 cases (an almost 4 fold increase), and by 26 Mar 2020 4 days later there were 56 188 cases -- a 4 day doubling time. A very sobering set of statistics, seeing how rapidly this virus is transmitted through the community.

A map of Spain showing provinces (autonomous communities) can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/spain-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7149046,43. La Rioja, Navarre, and Basque Country are located together in the north of the country. Madrid is in the northern part of central Spain. - Mod.MPP]

