[Yesterday (25 Mar 2020) I was very concerned about COVID-19 taking hold in Kinshasa, with an estimated population in 2018 of 13.2 million inhabitants (https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/EN.URB.LCTY?locations=CD). Today I am very concerned about the confirmation of a case in North Kivu, one of the main areas involved in the ebolavirus outbreak from 2018 to 2020, and especially because it is an area of extreme civil unrest, with a number of different rebel groups that were attacking ETUs (Ebola treatment units) and the population living in the area. The MOH announcement does not specify where in North Kivu the case was identified but 2 of the 3 major cities (Beni and Butembo) were areas of peak ebolavirus activity. Even though 54 days have passed since the last confirmed case of ebolavirus disease was identified (2 incubation periods is 42 days), the most recent WHO Disease Outbreak News update, today, 26 Mar 2020 says, "However, due to challenges related to continued insecurity and population displacement in previous hotspots, limited access to some affected communities, and potential shortages of resources amidst other local and global emergencies, there remains a high risk of re-emergence of the virus." (https://www.who.int/csr/don/26-March-2020-ebola-drc/en/) Thus, there are active outbreak and response activities ongoing in the area. I fear the consequences of an outbreak of COVID-19 in that zone.

Returning to the situation with COVID-19 in Kinshasa, 2 newly confirmed cases were reported there in the past 24 hours. No mention is made of transmission chains, if there are multiple importations, or established community-based local transmission.

A map of the Congo DR showing provinces can be found at https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/africasource/below-the-surface-a-game-changer-in-congolese-politics/ and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7149046,194. North Kivu is in the East of the country bordering with Rwanda and Uganda. Beni and Butembo are in the north of the province near the border with Ituri.- Mod.MPP]

